category: ALWAYS SAY NEVER
category comment: 

clue: Created by Bill Watterson, this comic strip kid says of class bully Moe, "Never argue with a 6-year-old who shaves"

response: Calvin

clue: Line that precedes "they simply fade away" in a British army song

response: old soldiers never die

clue: "He that fights and runs away may" these 5 words "but he that is in battle slain will never rise to fight again"

response: live to fight another day

clue: In his "Ballad of East and West", this Brit wrote, "East is east, and west is west, and never the twain shall meet"

response: Rudyard Kipling

clue: Shelley said of this, "Hail to thee, blithe spirit! Bird thou never wert"; Wordsworth said they "soar, but never roam"

response: skylark

